Directions.1: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).

Directions.2: Combine flour, sourdough starter discard, olive oil, rosemary, and kosher salt in a bowl. Mix with a wooden spoon to incorporate the ingredients. Turn out onto a work surface and knead until a smooth dough forms. Divide the dough into 2 pieces and shape each piece into a small rectangle.

Directions.3: Lightly flour a large sheet of parchment paper and place 1 piece of dough on top. Lightly flour top of dough, roll into a large, 1/16-inch thick rectangle, and cut into 1 1/4-inch squares. Spray tops with cooking spray and sprinkle with flaked sea salt. Carefully transfer the parchment paper and dough to a baking sheet. Repeat with remaining dough.

Directions.4: Bake in the preheated oven until crackers are golden brown, about 24 minutes, turning halfway through.

Directions.5: Remove from the oven and let cool on a baking rack.
